SendMessage is not available as a native tool. Since you are the team lead, I will present the complete design directly. Here is the full Error Recovery live screen design, built on the existing dashboard design system.

---

## Error Recovery Live Screen -- Complete UI Design

---

### 1. Backend Extensions Needed (WebSocket Events)

The current `ws.rs` broadcasts generic JSON strings. Three new event types are needed, plus one response type from client to server.

**New server-to-client events:**

```jsonc
// When the agent escalates (CAPTCHA, login, bot-block, paywall)
{
  "type": "agent_paused",
  "session_id": "sess_abc123",
  "goal_id": "goal_xyz",
  "reason": "CAPTCHA detected on checkout page",
  "page_type": "captcha",       // "captcha" | "login_wall" | "paywall" | "bot_block" | "max_errors"
  "page_url": "https://example.com/checkout",
  "step_count": 14,
  "sub_goal": "Complete payment form",
  "paused_at": "2026-06-06T14:32:01Z"
}

// Live screenshot frame (base64 PNG, sent ~2fps)
{
  "type": "screenshot_frame",
  "session_id": "sess_abc123",
  "data_base64": "iVBORw0KGgo...",
  "width": 1920,
  "height": 1080
}

// When the user clicks Resume and the agent continues
{
  "type": "agent_resumed",
  "session_id": "sess_abc123",
  "goal_id": "goal_xyz",
  "resumed_at": "2026-06-06T14:33:15Z"
}
```

**New client-to-server events (sent over the same WebSocket):**

```jsonc
// User clicks on the screenshot
{
  "type": "user_click",
  "session_id": "sess_abc123",
  "x": 450,
  "y": 320
}

// User types into the floating input
{
  "type": "user_type",
  "session_id": "sess_abc123",
  "text": "Hello"
}

// User presses a key (Enter, Tab, Escape, Backspace)
{
  "type": "user_key",
  "session_id": "sess_abc123",
  "key": "Enter"
}

// User resumes the agent
{
  "type": "resume_agent",
  "session_id": "sess_abc123"
}
```

**In `ws.rs`**, the `handle_socket` function needs to process `Message::Text` from the receiver and dispatch to the daemon (likely via the broadcast sender or a separate channel). The client-to-server messages map to gRPC calls: `click_at`, `type_text`, `press_key`, and a `resume_session` RPC.

---

### 2. HTML Structure

Insert these elements inside the `.container` div, directly before the closing `</div>` of `.container` (they are siblings to the header, status-strip, goal-bar, eyes-panel, and goals-grid):

```html
<!-- ============================================================ -->
<!-- ERROR RECOVERY: Live Screen Overlay                           -->
<!-- ============================================================ -->
<div id="liveOverlay" class="live-overlay hidden">
  <div class="live-panel glass">

    <!-- Pause Banner -->
    <div class="pause-banner" id="pauseBanner">
      <span class="pause-icon">&#9888;</span>
      <span class="pause-text" id="pauseText">AGENT PAUSED</span>
      <span class="pause-reason" id="pauseReason">CAPTCHA detected</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Screenshot Area -->
    <div class="screenshot-viewport" id="screenshotViewport">
      <img id="liveScreenshot" src="" alt="Live browser view"
           class="screenshot-img" draggable="false" />
      <!-- Click ripple container (absolutely positioned children) -->
      <div class="ripple-layer" id="rippleLayer"></div>
      <!-- Hover crosshair -->
      <div class="crosshair-overlay"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Action Bar -->
    <div class="action-bar">
      <div class="input-group">
        <input type="text" id="textInput" class="glass text-input"
