### 5. UX Flow (State Machine)

```
IDLE          →  agent_paused event    →  RECOVERY (overlay opens)
RECOVERY      →  screenshot_frame*     →  RECOVERY (update image, throttled)
RECOVERY      →  user clicks image     →  RECOVERY (ripple + send user_click)
RECOVERY      →  user types + Enter    →  RECOVERY (send user_type + user_key Enter)
RECOVERY      →  user clicks Resume    →  CLOSING (send resume_agent, hide overlay)
RECOVERY      →  user clicks Cancel    →  CLOSING (send cancel_goal, hide overlay)
RECOVERY      →  agent_resumed event   →  IDLE (confirmed resume)
CLOSING       →  N/A                   →  IDLE (overlay hidden, timer cleared)
IDLE          →  goal_update event     →  IDLE (dashboard updates normally)
```

Screenshot frames stream at approximately 2fps from the daemon while the overlay is visible. The `pressed` guard on the viewport prevents frame swaps during a mousedown period, avoiding visual jank when the user is trying to click a specific element.

